                  "title": "Credential Stuffing",
                  "status": "Open",
                  "severity": "High",
                  "type": "Spoofing",
                  "description": "Attacker uses leaked username and password lists to attempt login as valid users. No MFA exists to block unauthorized access even with correct credentials.",
                  "mitigation": "Enforce account lockout after 5 failed attempts. Add CAPTCHA on login form. Implement multi-factor authentication. Monitor logins from unusual IP addresses.",
